  "texts": [
    "Roughly speaking, the Merkle method provides a way to collect different values and represent the collected values with a \"root\" hash.",
    "Given this root hash, you can simply \"prove\" that an element exists in the given hash tree.",
    "And the size of the proof is paired with the number of leaf nodes.",
    "Merkle's method transforms a onetime signature into an n-order signature.",
    "Constructing this method is still based on some one-time signature method, such as the Lamport method which is still relatively expensive."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}